Greek Fiscal Measures May Include Wage Levy, Kathimerini Says

-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 
2011-06-05T08:56:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/greek-fiscal-measures-may-include-wage-levy-kathimerini-says.html
Greece ’s 6.4 billion-euro ($9.4
billion) package of budget cuts for the rest of this year will
include an increase in  sales tax  for restaurants and a 3 percent
levy on state workers’ wages to subsidize  unemployment benefits ,
Kathimerini reported.  The government will consider streamlining taxes in
September, including lowering the corporate rate to 15 percent
from 20 percent, the  Athens-based newspaper  said, without saying
how it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Petrakis in Athens at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at   acullen8@bloomberg.net  